sources.title: Frontier Days (1934) BILL CODY
sources.description:
Stars: Bill Cody, Ada Ince, Wheeler Oakman
Director: Robert F. Hill (as Robert Hill)

While investigating cattle rustlers, The Pinto Kid gets in a mess of trouble when accidentally drops his glove at a murder scene.

TRIVIA: Born William Joseph Cody on January 5, 1891, in St. Paul, Minnesota, he became a popular cowboy star during the 1920s and 1930s. Cody is often associated with the B-Western genre, where he played the heroic cowboy figure, a staple of American cinema during that period.

sources.title: Frontier Days (1934) Action, Adventure, Romance Full Length Movie
sources.description:
Henry Jethrow is after the Wilson ranch. He has George Wilson unknowingly sign a note for the ranch, has him killed, and then presents the note. The Pinto Kid, investigating cattle rustlers, accidentally drops his glove at the murder scene and now has a price on his head.

Director: Robert F. Hill 
Writers: Norman Springer, Robert F. Hill 
Stars: Bill Cody, Ada Ince, Wheeler Oakman
Genres: Classics, Action, Adventure, Romance, Western

metadata.Plot: Henry Jethrow is after the Wilson ranch. He has George Wilson unknowningly sign a note for the ranch, has him killed, and then presents the note. The Pinto Kid, investigating cattle rustlers, accidentally drops his glove at the murder scene and now has a price on his head. He has Beth Wilson turn him and use the reward money to reclaim the note. Now he has to escape jail and find the real killers.
